      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are fork tender, drain and return to the pot</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with a small knob of<strong> butter</strong>, the <strong>remaining Dijon mustard</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>and the<strong> chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Return the pot to a low heat and cook for 1-2 min or until the butter has melted and the garlic is fragrant – this is your <strong>warm garlic & parsley potato salad</strong></p>",
